Results.ReviewText: we recently got back from a weekend camping trip but with 4 kids and a dog the car was pretty packed so i was trying desperately trying to figure out how i was going to enjoy my morning fix without having to pack an entire jar when i saw these in asda i had noticed the 3 in 1 sachets in the past but i dont take sugar so was really happy when i spotted th 2 in 1 :) perfect amount of coffee and milk blend they were an essential part of our weekend and will be taken with us from now on

Results.ReviewText:
Have been using these for years now, camping, caravanning, days out, long journeys and at home. They makes a nice cup of coffee with no sugar.
A warning however, there is a new version out in some shops, looks the same but says "Coffee & Creamer" instead of "Original" They are nasty, very weak tasting and leave a taste in your mouth for ages. Please Nescafe, don't change to these!
Results.Title: Very useful indeed!

Results.ReviewText: We have recently switched to Nescafe Original 2-in-1 as we were finding our usual brand too 'scummy' and somewhat tasteless.  We love the taste of Nescafe and personally I drink the whole cup now rather than leaving half of it as with our former brand.  It's a lifesaver when we visit the grandchildren to babysit and need a quick reviving drink!
Results.Title: Our 'Nes'sential cup of coffee!
